that's his son. Yes, yes, yes. Did you go to any 
religious events here while you were a student?

28:55.331 --> 28:56.333
Did you go to church?

28:59.839 --> 29:01.963
Well, occasionally I would. Where did you? I'd go 
to the Episcopal Church. At South? We were raised

29:06.762 --> 29:13.909
in the Eastern Orthodox Church. And that's where 
my Sunday school teacher told me the earth was

29:15.411 --> 29:21.437
5,000 years old. So they didn't have any Eastern 
Orthodox Church in this area. So Episcopal

29:28.524 --> 29:36.212
services and rites are the same as practically of 
the others. Were there any Sunday night church

29:36.530 --> 29:42.537
meetings? Not that I remember. Oh, they had 
meetings, but I don't know. Was Religious

29:46.701 --> 29:49.644
Emphasis Week held in that era? In the late 30s, I 
know they had here on the campus one week in the

29:51.126 --> 29:58.754
spring when they would have ministers from all 
